{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "jira-mock-v2-collection-2025",
    "name": "Jira Mock API v2 – Training Collection",
    "description": "# Jira Mock API – Student Training Collection\n\nUse this collection to practice interacting with the Jira Mock Service running locally.\n\n## 🔑 Authentication\nEvery API request requires:\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer mock-jira-token-2025\n```\nThis is already configured in the **Jira Mock – Local** environment. Just select it and you're good to go.\n\n## 🚀 Quick Start\n1. Import this collection **and** the `Jira_Mock_v2.postman_environment.json` file\n2. Select the **Jira Mock – Local** environment (top-right dropdown)\n3. Make sure the Jira Mock server is running on `http://localhost:4001`\n4. Run **Health Check** first to verify the server is up\n5. Run **Create Story** — the response `key` is auto-saved to `{{created_story_key}}`\n6. Use that variable in **Read Story**, **Edit Story**, etc.\n\n## 📚 API Groups\n- **System** — health check\n- **Story** — create, read, edit (PUT), edit (PATCH), delete, transition\n- **Bug** — create, read, edit (PUT), edit (PATCH), delete, transition\n- **Search** — list all, filter by type, filter by status (JQL)\n- **Admin** — reset database to seed data",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{api_token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [],
  "item": [

    {
      "name": "System",
      "description": "Service health and metadata",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/health",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Verify the Jira Mock server is running. No auth required."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
              "body": "{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"service\": \"jira-mock\",\n  \"version\": \"2.0.0\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "Story",
      "description": "CRUD operations for Story issue type.\n\nAll requests use:\n`Authorization: Bearer {{api_token}}`",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "Create Story",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.environment.set('created_story_key', json.key);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('issue_key', json.key);",
                  "    console.log('Story created:', json.key);",
                  "    pm.test('Story created with 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "    pm.test('Key starts with QA-', () => pm.expect(json.key).to.match(/^QA-/));",
                  "    pm.test('Issue type is Story', () => pm.expect(json.fields.issuetype.name).to.eql('Story'));",
                  "    pm.test('Story points set', () => pm.expect(json.fields.customfield_10016).to.eql(5));",
                  "    pm.test('Sprint set', () => pm.expect(json.fields.customfield_10020[0].name).to.eql('Sprint 1'));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fields\": {\n    \"project\": {\"key\": \"QA\"},\n    \"summary\": \"User can log in with valid credentials\",\n    \"description\": \"As a user, I want to log in to the application so that I can access my dashboard.\\n\\nACCEPTANCE CRITERIA\\nAC1 - Given I enter valid credentials, when I click Login, then I am redirected to the dashboard.\\nAC2 - Given I enter an invalid password, then I see an error message 'Invalid credentials'.\\nAC3 - Given I leave the username empty, then I see a 'Required' validation message.\",\n    \"issuetype\": {\"name\": \"Story\"},\n    \"priority\": {\"name\": \"High\"},\n    \"assignee\": \"jane.smith\",\n    \"labels\": [\"auth\", \"ui\"],\n    \"components\": [{\"name\": \"Frontend\"}],\n    \"customfield_10016\": 5,\n    \"customfield_10020\": \"Sprint 1\",\n    \"customfield_10014\": null\n  }\n}",
              "options": {"raw": {"language": "json"}}
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/rest/api/3/issue",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["rest", "api", "3", "issue"]
            },
            "description": "Create a new Story.\n\n**Auto-saves** the created issue `key` to `{{created_story_key}}` and `{{issue_key}}` environment variables.\n\n### Story-specific fields\n| Field | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| `customfield_10016` | Story Points (integer) |\n| `customfield_10020` | Sprint name (string) |\n| `customfield_10014` | Epic Link – key of parent epic |\n\n**Auth:** `Bearer {{api_token}}`"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "201 Created",
              "status": "Created",
              "code": 201,
              "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
              "body": "{\n  \"id\": \"8\",\n  \"key\": \"QA-8\",\n  \"self\": \"/rest/api/3/issue/QA-8\",\n  \"fields\": {\n    \"project\": {\"key\": \"QA\", \"name\": \"QA Project\"},\n    \"summary\": \"User can log in with valid credentials\",\n    \"description\": {\n      \"type\": \"doc\", \"version\": 1,\n      \"content\": [{\"type\": \"paragraph\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"As a user...\"}]}]\n    },\n    \"issuetype\": {\"name\": \"Story\"},\n    \"priority\": {\"name\": \"High\"},\n    \"status\": {\"name\": \"To Do\", \"statusCategory\": {\"name\": \"To Do\"}},\n    \"assignee\": {\"accountId\": \"jane.smith\", \"displayName\": \"jane.smith\"},\n    \"reporter\": {\"accountId\": \"mock-reporter\", \"displayName\": \"mock-reporter\"},\n    \"created\": \"2025-09-06 12:00:00\",\n    \"updated\": \"2025-09-06 12:00:00\",\n    \"labels\": [\"auth\", \"ui\"],\n    \"components\": [],\n    \"customfield_10016\": 5,\n    \"customfield_10020\": [{\"id\": 1, \"name\": \"Sprint 1\", \"state\": \"active\"}],\n    \"customfield_10014\": null,\n    \"environment\": null,\n    \"fixVersions\": [],\n    \"duedate\": null\n  }\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "401 Unauthorized",
              "status": "Unauthorized",
              "code": 401,
              "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
              "body": "{\n  \"detail\": \"Invalid token. Only the mock API token is accepted. See /docs for the correct token.\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },

