              "raw": "{\n  \"fields\": {\n    \"project\": {\"key\": \"QA\"},\n    \"summary\": \"Login button unresponsive on first click in Safari\",\n    \"description\": \"When using Safari 17 on iOS, the login button does not respond on the first tap. A second tap is required to trigger authentication.\\n\\nSteps to Reproduce:\\n1. Open Safari 17 on iOS 17\\n2. Navigate to the login page\\n3. Enter valid credentials\\n4. Tap the Login button once\\n\\nExpected: User is authenticated and redirected to dashboard.\\nActual: Nothing happens. Second tap works.\",\n    \"issuetype\": {\"name\": \"Bug\"},\n    \"priority\": {\"name\": \"Critical\"},\n    \"assignee\": \"bob.tester\",\n    \"labels\": [\"safari\", \"ios\", \"regression\"],\n    \"components\": [{\"name\": \"Frontend\"}],\n    \"environment\": \"Production – Safari 17, iOS 17.4, iPhone 15 Pro\",\n    \"fixVersions\": [{\"name\": \"v1.3.1\"}, {\"name\": \"v1.4.0\"}],\n    \"duedate\": \"2025-10-31\"\n  }\n}",
              "options": {"raw": {"language": "json"}}
